<p>Having reached 'finals day' of the indoor cricket league last year, JBCC has shown itself to be a competitive club, and with much of last year's squad intact we will be looking to build upon this in 2015.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>We compete in two competitions, with two sides entering the indoor six-a-side league in those long, dark winter months, and one side entering the T20 outdoor league when the sun finally comes out in summer term.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you're interested in joining the club then come to our taster session in the Howlands at 11am on Monday 29th September, come and see us at the Freshers Fair, or contact either Rowan or James using the details below.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>President - Rowan Bird</p><p><a href="mailto:r.j.bird@durham.ac.uk">r.j.bird@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>Captain - James West</p><p><a href="mailto:j.a.a.west@durham.ac.uk">j.a.a.west@durham.ac.uk</a></p>